{"title_page": "Zsolt Szeglet", "text_new": "{{eastern name order|Szeglet Zsolt}}\n\n'''Zsolt Szeglet''' (born 4 May 1977 in [[Keszthely]], [[Zala County|Zala]]) is a [[Hungary|Hungarian]] athlete specializing in the [[400 metres]].\n\n== Professional career ==\nHe finished fifth at the [[2002 European Championships in Athletics]], and participated in the Olympic Games in [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000]] and [[2004 Summer Olympics|2004]]. Szeglet finished seventh with the Hungarian [[4 x 100 metres relay]] team, which consisted of [[Viktor Kov\u00e1cs]], [[G\u00e1bor Dobos]], [[Roland N\u00e9meth]] and Szeglet, at the [[1999 World Championships in Athletics|1999 World Championships]].\n\nHis personal best time over 400 m is 45.43 seconds, achieved in May 2001 in [[College Station, TX|College Station]].\n\n==External links==\n* At one point he also wished to play for [http://www.forestforum.co.uk \"Nottingham Forest Football Club]\n* {{IAAF|137428}}\n* {{SR/Olympics profile|sz/zsolt-szeglet-1}}\n* {{IOC profile|zsolt-szeglet}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Footer Hungarian Athletics Championships winners in Men's 400 metres}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Szeglet, Zsolt}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male sprinters]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2000 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of Hungary]]\n\n\n{{Hungary-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{eastern name order|Szeglet Zsolt}}\n\n'''Zsolt Szeglet''' (born 4 May 1977 in [[Keszthely]], [[Zala County|Zala]]) is a [[Hungary|Hungarian]] athlete specializing in the [[400 metres]].\n\n== Professional career ==\nHe finished fifth at the [[2002 European Championships in Athletics]], and participated in the Olympic Games in [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000]] and [[2004 Summer Olympics|2004]]. Szeglet finished seventh with the Hungarian [[4 x 100 metres relay]] team, which consisted of [[Viktor Kov\u00e1cs]], [[G\u00e1bor Dobos]], [[Roland N\u00e9meth]] and Szeglet, at the [[1999 World Championships in Athletics|1999 World Championships]].\n\nHis personal best time over 400 m is 45.43 seconds, achieved in May 2001 in [[College Station, TX|College Station]].\n\n==External links==\n* At one point he also wished to play for [http://www.forestforum.co.uk \"Nottingham Forest Football Club]\n* {{IAAF|137428}}\n* {{SR/Olympics profile|sz/zsolt-szeglet-1}}\n* {{IOC profile|zsolt-szeglet}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{Footer Hungarian Athletics Championships winners in Men's 400 metres}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Szeglet, Zsolt}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male sprinters]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2000 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of Hungary]]\n\n\n{{Hungary-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Update date format tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zsolt_Szeglet"}
